6-Chloroalkylbenzoimidazo[1,2-c]quinazolines 8 and 9 were obtained by acylation of compound 3 with the chloroacylclorides in glacial acetic acid at 60 °C (Scheme 2
) as described previously [40]. Compound 8 was treated with various secondary amines in DMF at room temperature for 24 h to give the benzoimidazo[1,2-c]quinazolines 10a–10e (Scheme 2). This method failed in case of the preparation of 11a–11e (n
 = 2). On the other hand, the attempts to prepare 11a by refluxing compound 9 with an excess of piperidine in ethanol resulted in the formation of significant amount of compounds 5 and 7a (by TLC approx. <20% and approx. <60% respectively), though the desired product 11a was also present in the reaction mixture. Similar results were observed under transformation of 9 to 11b–11e.
